[I] Linux Userspace x86_64 Emulator with a twist, targeted at ARM64

[T] Box64 lets you run x86_64 Linux programs (such as games) on non-x86_64
[T] Linux systems, like ARM (host system needs to be 64-bit little-endian).

[U] https://github.com/ptitSeb/box64/

[A] Sebastien Chevalier
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/emulator
[F] CROSS
[R] + arm64 powerpc64 riscv64

